        [ B "Ascendant (Legendary)."
        , T " The Ascendant focus has the Slumbering, Stirring, and Wakened properties. In addition, when you cast a spell of 1st level or higher while holding this focus, you can treat the spell as if it were cast using a 9th-level spell slot. Once this property is used, it can't be used again until the next dawn."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Dried Leech"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:dried-leech"
    , rarity: [RarityUncommon]
    , itemtype: TypeWeapon (Just "any ammunition")
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceBookOfManyThings]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Weapon (any ammunition), uncommon"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "This leech has been dried and imbued with a mote of animating magic. If you hit a creature with a ranged attack roll using this ammunition, the leech springs to life and sinks its teeth into the target, dealing 1d4 piercing damage at the start of each of the target's turns. If the leech deals at least 10 damage or the target dies, the leech falls off. A creature, including the target, can use its action to detach the leech. Once a leech is no longer attached to its target, the leech dies and is no longer magical."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Driftglobe"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:driftglobe"
    , rarity: [RarityUncommon]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceDMG]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, uncommon"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "This small sphere of thick glass weighs 1 pound. If you are within 60 feet of it, you can speak its command word and cause it to emanate the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:light" "Light"
        , T " or "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:daylight" "Daylight"
        , T " spell. Once used, the Daylight effect can't be used again until the next dawn."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "You can speak another command word as an action to make the illuminated globe rise into the air and float no more than 5 feet off the ground. The globe hovers in this way until you or another creature grasps it. If you move more than 60 feet from the hovering globe, it follows you until it is within 60 feet of you. It takes the shortest route to do so. If prevented from moving, the globe sinks gently to the ground and becomes inactive, and its light winks out."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Dust of Corrosion"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:dust-of-corrosion"
    , rarity: [RarityUncommon]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceTheWildBeyondTheWitchlight]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous Item, Uncommon"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "As an action, you can throw this dust into the air, filling a 10-foot cube that extends out from you. Surfaces and objects made of nonmagical ferrous metal in the area instantly corrode and turn to dust, becoming useless and unsalvageable. Any creature in the area that is made wholly or partly out of ferrous metal must make a DC 13 Constitution saving throw, taking 4d8 necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Found in a small packet, this dust is made from finely ground rust monster antennae. There is enough dust in each packet for one use."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Dust of Deliciousness"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:dust-of-deliciousness"
    , rarity: [RarityUncommon]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceExplorersGuideToWildemount]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, uncommon"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "This reddish brown dust can be sprinkled over any edible substance to greatly improve the flavor. The dust also dulls the eater's senses: anyone eating food treated with this dust has disadvantage on Wisdom ability checks and Wisdom saving throws for 1 hour. There is enough dust to flavor six servings."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Dust of Disappearance"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:dust-of-disappearance"
    , rarity: [RarityUncommon]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceDMG]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, uncommon"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Found in a small packet, this powder resembles very fine sand. There is enough of it for one use. When you use an action to throw the dust into the air, you and each creature and object within 10 feet of you become invisible for 2d4 minutes. The duration is the same for all subjects, and the dust is consumed when its magic takes effect. If a creature affected by the dust attacks or casts a spell, the invisibility ends for that creature."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Dust of Dryness"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:dust-of-dryness"
    , rarity: [RarityUncommon]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceDMG]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, uncommon"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "This small packet contains 1d6 + 4 pinches of dust. You can use an action to sprinkle a pinch of it over water. The dust turns a cube of water 15 feet on a side into one marble-sized pellet, which floats or rests near where the dust was sprinkled. The pellet's weight is negligible."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Someone can use an action to smash the pellet against a hard surface, causing the pellet to shatter and release the water the dust absorbed. Doing so ends that pellet's magic."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "An elemental composed mostly of water that is exposed to a pinch of the dust must make a DC 13 Constitution saving throw, taking 10d6 necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Dust of Sneezing and Choking"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:dust-of-sneezing-and-choking"
    , rarity: [RarityUncommon]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceDMG]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, uncommon"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Found in a small container, this powder resembles very fine sand. It appears to be "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/wondrous-items:dust-of-disappearance" "Dust of Disappearance"
        , T ", and an "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:identify" "Identify"
        , T " spell reveals it to be such. There is enough of it for one use."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "When you use an action to throw a handful of the dust into the air, you and each creature that needs to breathe within 30 feet of you must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or become unable to breathe, while sneezing uncontrollably. A creature affected in this way is incapacitated and suffocating. As long as it is conscious, a creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on it on a success. The "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:lesser-restoration" "Lesser Restoration"
        , T " spell can also end the effect on a creature."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Earworm"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:earworm"
    , rarity: [RarityUncommon]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceEberronRisingFromTheLastWar]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "To attune to this symbiont, you must hold it against the skin behind your ear for the entire attunement period, whereupon it burrows into your head and bonds to your skull. While the "
        , I "earworm"
        , T " is inside you, you can speak, read, and write Deep Speech."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Spells."
        , T " The "
        , I "earworm"
        , T " has 4 charges. You can cast the following spells from it, expending the necessary number of charges (spell save DC 15): "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:detect-thoughts" "Detect Thoughts"
        , T " (2 charges) or "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:dissonant-whispers" "Dissonant Whispers"
        , T " (1 charge). Each time you use the "
        , I "earworm"
        , T " to cast the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:detect-thoughts" "Detect Thought"
        , T " spell, it sends the information gleaned to the nearest daelkyr, or to the next nearest "
        , I "earworm"
        , T " until it reaches a daelkyr."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The "
        , I "earworm"
        , T " regains 1d4 expended charges daily at dawn."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Symbiotic Nature."
        , T " The "
        , I "earworm"
        , T " can't be removed from you while you're attuned to it, and you can't voluntarily end your attunement to it. If you're targeted by a spell that ends a curse, your attunement to the earworm ends, and it exits your body."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Eldritch Claw Tattoo"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:eldritch-claw-tattoo"
    , rarity: [RarityUncommon]
    , itemtype: TypeItem (Just "tattoo")
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceTashasCauldronOfEverything]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item (tattoo), uncommon (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Produced by a special needle, this magic tattoo depicts clawlike forms and other jagged shapes."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Tattoo Attunement."
        , T " To attune to this item, you hold the needle to your skin where you want the tattoo to appear, pressing the needle there throughout the attunement process. When the attunement is complete, the needle turns into the ink that becomes the tattoo, which appears on the skin."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "If your attunement to the tattoo ends, the tattoo vanishes, and the needle reappears in your space."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Magical Strikes."
        , T " While the tattoo is on your skin, your unarmed strikes are considered magical for the purpose of overcoming immunity and resistance to nonmagical attacks, and you gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls with unarmed strikes."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Eldritch Maul."
        , T " As a bonus action, you can empower the tattoo for 1 minute. For the duration, each of your melee attacks with a weapon or an unarmed strike can reach a target up to 15 feet away from you, as inky tendrils launch toward the target. In addition, your melee attacks deal an extra 1d6 force damage on a hit. Once used, this bonus action can't be used again until the next dawn."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Elemental Gem"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:elemental-gem"
    , rarity: [RarityUncommon]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceDMG]
    , description:
      [ P
