    , attunement: Attune (Just "creature that has proficiency in the arcana skill")
    , source: [SourceWaterdeepDungeonOfTheMadMage]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous Item, Legendary (requires attunement by a creature that has proficiency in the Arcana skill)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Any creature that attunes to the tablet must make a DC 20 Wisdom saving throw at the end of its next long rest. On a failed save, the creature becomes afflicted with a random form of long-term madness (see \"Madness\" in chapter 8 of the Dungeon Master's Guide)."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "As an action, a creature attuned to the "
        , I "Black Crystal Tablet"
        , T " can use it to cast "
        , I "Eyebite"
        , T " or "
        , I "Gate"
        , T " (the portal created by this spell links to the Far Realm only). After the tablet is used to cast a spell, it cannot be used again until the next dawn."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Blackrazor"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:blackrazor"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeWeapon (Just "greatsword")
    , attunement: Attune (Just "creature of non-lawful alignment")
    , source: [SourceDMG]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Weapon (greatsword), legendary (requires attunement by a creature of non-lawful alignment)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Hidden in the dungeon of White Plume Mountain, "
        , I "Blackrazor"
        , T " shines like a piece of night sky filled with stars. Its black scabbard is decorated with pieces of cut obsidian."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "You gain a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. It has the following additional properties."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Devour Soul."
        , T " Whenever you use it to reduce a creature to 0 hit points, the sword slays the creature and devours its soul, unless it is a construct or an undead. A creature whose soul has been devoured by "
        , I "Blackrazor"
        , T " can be restored to life only by a "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:wish" "Wish"
        , T " spell."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "When it devours a soul, "
        , I "Blackrazor"
        , T " grants you temporary hit points equal to the slain creature's hit point maximum. These hit points fade after 24 hours. As long as these temporary hit points last and you keep "
        , I "Blackrazor"
        , T " in hand, you have advantage on attack rolls, saving throws, and ability checks."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "If you hit an undead with this weapon, you take 1d10 necrotic damage and the target regains 1d10 hit points. If this necrotic damage reduces you to 0 hit points, "
        , I "Blackrazor"
        , T " devours your soul."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Soul Hunter."
        , T " While you hold the weapon. you are aware of the presence of Tiny or larger creatures within 60 feet of you that aren't constructs or undead. You also can't be charmed or frightened."
        ]
      , P
        [ I "Blackrazor"
        , T " can cast the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:haste" "Haste"
        , T " spell on you once per day. It decides when to cast the spell and maintains concentration on it so that you don't have to."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Sentience."
        , I "Blackrazor"
        , T " is a sentient chaotic neutral weapon with an Intelligence of 17, a Wisdom of 10, and a Charisma of 19. It has hearing and darkvision out to a range of 120 feet."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The weapon can speak, read, and understand Common, and can communicate with its wielder telepathically. Its voice is deep and echoing. While you are attuned to it, "
        , I "Blackrazor"
        , T " also understands every language you know."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Personality."
        , I "Blackrazor"
        , T " speaks with an imperious tone, as though accustomed to being obeyed. The sword's purpose is to consume souls. It doesn't care whose souls it eats, including the wielder's. The sword believes that all matter and energy sprang from a void of negative energy and will one day return to it. "
        , I "Blackrazor"
        , T " is meant to hurry that process along."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Despite its nihilism, "
        , I "Blackrazor"
        , T " feels a strange kinship to Wave and Whelm, two other weapons locked away under White Plume Mountain. It wants the three weapons to be united again and wielded together in combat, even though it violently disagrees with "
        , I "Whelm"
        , T " and finds "
        , I "Wave"
        , T " tedious."
        ]
      , P
        [ I "Blackrazor's"
        , T " hunger for souls must be regularly fed. If the sword goes three days or more without consuming a soul, a conflict between it and its wielder occurs at the next sunset."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Blackstaff"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:blackstaff"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeStaff
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceWaterdeepDragonHeist]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Staff, legendary (requires attunement by the Blackstaff heir, who must be a wizard)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The "
        , I "Blackstaff"
        , T " is a sentient, rune-carved staff set with thin silver veins. It is the symbol of office for the Blackstaff, the highest ranking wizard in Waterdeep. As the rightful owner of the "
        , I "Blackstaff"
        , T ", Vajra Safahr is the only one who can become attuned to it. The staff can, however, choose a new owner (see \"Personality\" below)."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The "
        , I "Blackstaff"
        , T " has the magical properties of a "
        , I "staff of power"
        , T " in addition to the following properties."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Animate Walking Statues."
        , T " You can expend 1 or more of the staff's charges as an action to animate or deactivate one or more of the walking statues of Waterdeep. You must be in the city to use this property, and you can animate or deactivate one statue for each charge expended. An animated statue obeys the telepathic commands of Khelben Arunsun's spirit, which is trapped inside the staff (see \"Personality\" below). A walking statue becomes inanimate if deactivated or if the staff is broken."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Dispel Magic."
        , T " You can expend 1 of the staff's charges as a bonus action to cast "
        , I "dispel magic"
        , T " on a creature, an object, or a magical effect that you touch with the tip of the staff. If the target is an unwilling creature or an object in the possession of such a creature, you must hit the creature with a melee attack using the "
        , I "Blackstaff"
        , T " before you can expend the charge to cast the spell."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Drain Magic."
        , T " This property affects only creatures that use spell slots. When you hit such a creature with a melee attack using the "
        , I "Blackstaff"
        , T ", you can expend 1 of the staff's charges as a bonus action, causing the target to expend one spell slot of the highest spell level it can cast without casting a spell. If the target has already expended all its spell slots, nothing happens. Spell slots that are expended in this fashion are regained when the target finishes a long rest, as normal."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Master of Enchantment."
        , T " When you cast an enchantment spell of 1st level or higher while holding the staff, you can make an Intelligence (Arcana) check with a DC of 10 + the level of the spell. If the check succeeds, you cast the spell without expending a spell slot."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Sentience."
        , T " The "
        , I "Blackstaff"
        , T " is a sentient staff of neutral alignment, with an Intelligence of 22, a Wisdom of 15, and a Charisma of 18. It has hearing and darkvision out to a range of 120 feet, and it can communicate telepathically with any creature that is holding it."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Personality."
        , T " The staff has the spirits of all previous Blackstaffs trapped within it. Its creator, Khelben Arunsun, is the dominant personality among them. Like Khelben, the staff is extremely devious and manipulative. It prefers to counsel its owner without exerting outright control. The staff's primary goal is to protect Waterdeep and its Open Lord, currently Laeral Silverhand. Its secondary goal is to help its wielder become more powerful."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "In the event that the holder of the office of the Blackstaff no longer serves the staff's wishes, the staff ceases to function until it finds a worthy inheritor-someone whose loyalty to Waterdeep is beyond reproach."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Spirit Trap."
        , T " When the Blackstaff dies, the spirit of that individual becomes trapped in the staff along with the spirits of the previous Blackstaffs. (A Blackstaff whose spirit is trapped in the staff can't be raised from the dead.)"
        ]
      , P
