        , T " has a sea-green jewel just below the tines and a silver shell at the end of its haft. It floats on the surface if dropped onto water, and it floats in place if it is released underwater. The trident is always cool to the touch, and it is immune to any damage due to exposure to water. "
        , I "Drown"
        , T " contains a spark of Olhydra, the Princess of Evil Water."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "You gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls you make with this magic weapon. When you hit with it, the targets takes an extra 1d8 cold damage."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Water Mastery."
        , T " You gain the following benefits while you hold "
        , I "Drown"
        , T ":"
        ]
      , UL
        [ [ T "You can speak Aquan fluently." ]
        , [ T "You have resistance to cold damage." ]
        , [ T "You can cast "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:dominate-monster" "Dominate Monster"
          , T " (save DC 17) on a water elemental. Once you have done so, "
          , I "Drown"
          , T " can't be used this way again until the next dawn."
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Tears of Endless Anguish."
        , T " While inside a water node, you can perform a ritual called the Tears of Endless Anguish, using "
        , I "Drown"
        , T " to create a "
        , I "devastation orb of water"
        , T " (see the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/wondrous-items:devastation-orb" "Devastation Orb"
        , T " description for the time and cost of the ritual). Once you perform the ritual, "
        , I "Drown"
        , T " can't be used to perform the ritual again until the next dawn."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Flaw."
        , I "Drown"
        , T " makes its wielder covetous. While attuned to the weapon, you gain the following flaw: \"I demand and deserve the largest share of the spoils, and I refuse to part with anything that's mine.\" In addition, if you are attuned to "
