      , P
        [ T "You can use an action to unfold and place the "
        , I "Hammock of Worlds"
        , T " on a solid surface, whereupon it creates a two-way portal to the Ghost Orchid Tepui in the Feywild or to the Drought Elder in the Far Realm (the user's choice). You can use an action to close an open portal by taking hold of the edges of the cloth and folding it up. Once the "
        , I "Hammock of Worlds"
        , T " has opened a portal, it can't do so again for 1d8 hours."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Harp of Gilded Plenty"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:harp-of-gilded-plenty"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceBigbyPresentsGloryOfTheGiants]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous Item, Legendary (Requires Attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "This golden harp is sculpted in the image of the god Iallanis, depicted as a young cloud giant woman. When a creature comes within 5 feet of the harp, the instrument animates and is capable of speaking, singing, and playing by itself."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Whenever you attempt to attune to the harp, you must first make either a DC 15 Charisma (Performance) check or a DC 20 Charisma (Persuasion) check to convince the harp that you are worthy, attuning to the harp on a success. If you fail, you can't attempt to attune to the harp again until the next dawn. Once you have successfully attuned to the harp, the harp resizes to suit you."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Stalwart Song."
        , T " Whenever you make a Charisma check while attuned to the harp, you can treat a roll of 9 or lower on the die as a 10."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Feast of Plenty."
        , T " If you spend 10 minutes playing the harp, you can cast the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:heroes-feast" "Heroes' Feast"
        , T " spell from it. Once this property is used, it can't be used again until 1d10 + 10 days have passed."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Soothing Melody."
        , T " As an action, you can use the harp to cast the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:calm-emotions" "Calm Emotions"
        , T " spell (save DC 19). When the spell is cast using the harp, its duration increases to 1 hour, provided you maintain concentration on the spell. This property can be used five times, and it regains all uses at dawn."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Sentience."
        , T " The harp is a sentient, chaotic good object with an Intelligence of 13, a Wisdom of 15, and a Charisma of 20. It has hearing and "
        , I "darkvision"
        , T " to a range of 120 feet."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The harp can speak, read, and understand Common and Giant. It can also communicate telepathically with the creature attuned to it."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The harp has a dramatic and pompous personality, taking extreme pride in the quality of music produced from its strings. If the harp is shorter than 6 feet tall, it bemoans its height."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Hazirawn"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:hazirawn"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeWeapon (Just "greatsword")
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceTyrannyOfDragons]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Weapon (greatsword), legendary (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "A sentient (neutral evil) greatsword, Hazirawn is capable of speech in Common and Netherese. Even if you aren't attuned to the sword, you gain a +1 bonus on attack rolls and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. If you aren't attuned to Hazirawn, you deal an extra 1d6 necrotic damage when you hit with it."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Increased Potency."
        , T " While you are attuned to this weapon, its bonus on attack rolls and damage rolls increases to +2, and a hit deals an extra 2d6 necrotic damage (instead of 1d6)."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Spells."
        , T " Hazirawn has 4 charges to cast spells. As long as the sword is attuned to you and you are holding it in your hand, you can use an action to expend the required number of charges to cast one of the following spells from the sword: "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:detect-magic" "Detect Magic"
        , T " (1 charge), "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:detect-evil-and-good" "Detect Evil and Good"
        , T " (1 charge), or "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:detect-thoughts" "Detect Thoughts"
        , T " (2 charges). Each night at midnight, Hazirawn regains 1d4 expended charges."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Wounding."
        , T " While you are attuned to the weapon, any creature that you hit with Hazirawn can't regain hit points for 1 minute. The target can make a DC 15 Constitution saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending this effect early on itself on a success."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Helm of Disjunction"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:helm-of-disjunction"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune (Just "sorcerer, warlock, or wizard")
    , source: [SourceDungeonsAndDragonsHonorAmongThieves]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous Item, legendary (requires attunement by a Sorcerer, Warlock, or Wizard)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The wizard Mordenkainen crafted this sleek, golden helmet. If he created other helms of disjunction, they have yet to be found."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "As an action while wearing this helm, you can use it to emit an antimagic pulse in a 300-foot-radius sphere centered on yourself. The pulse has the following effects:"
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Magic Item Disjunction."
        , T " Potions and scrolls in the area are destroyed. All other magic items in the area have their magical properties suppressed for 1 minute. Artifacts are unaffected by this property, as are magic items on your person."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Spell Disjunction."
        , T " Any ongoing spell ends if the creature, object, or area affected by it is even partly in the pulse's area."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Wave of Force."
        , T " The antimagic pulse is strong enough to knock down creatures close to you. Each creature within 30 feet of you must succeed on a DC 15 Strength saving throw or have the prone condition."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Once you use the helm's property, it can't be used again until 1d4 days have passed."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Helm of the Scavenger"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:helm-of-the-scavenger"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune (Just "spellcaster")
    , source: [SourceWaterdeepDungeonOfTheMadMage]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous Item, Legendary (requires attunement by a spellcaster)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "This ornate chair is designed to propel and maneuver a ship through space."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Passive Properties."
        , T " The following properties of the helm come into play even when no creature is attuned to it:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "When placed aboard a vessel weighing between 1 and 100 tons, the helm generates an envelope of fresh air around the ship while it is in the void of space (but not underwater). This envelope extends out from the edges of the hull in all directions for a distance equal in length to the vessel's beam, so that creatures aboard or near the ship can breath normally in space. The temperature within the air envelope is 70 degrees Fahrenheit."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "When placed aboard a vessel weighing between 1 and 100 tons, the helm generates an artificial gravity field while the ship is in the void of space, so that creatures can walk on the ships decks as they normally would. Creatures and objects that fall overboard bob in a gravity plane that extends out from the main deck for a distance equal in length to the vessel's beam."
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Active Properties."
        , T " The sensation of being attuned to the helm is akin to being immersed in warm water. While attuned to the helm you gain the following abilities while you sit in it:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "You can use the helm to propel the vessel across or through water and other liquids at a maximum speed in miles per hour equal to your highest-level unexpended spell slot."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "You can use the helm to propel the vessel through air or space at a maximum speed in miles per hour equal to your highest-level unexpended spell slot x 10."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Provided you have at least one unexpended spell slot, you can steer the vessel, albeit in a somewhat clumsy fashion, in much the same way that oars or a rudder can maneuver a seafaring ship."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Whenever you like, you can see what's happening on and around the vessel as though you were standing in a location of your choice aboard it."
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Drawback."
        , T " While attuned to the helm, you cannot expend your own spell slots."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Heretic"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:heretic"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeWeapon (Just "longsword")
    , attunement: Attune (Just "non-good creature")
    , source: [SourceQuestsFromTheInfiniteStaircase]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Weapon (longsword), legendary (requires attunement by a non-good creature)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The blasphemous weapon Heretic was created by a cult to steal power from good-aligned gods. The blade hungers to strike down servants of the Upper Planes and weaken the forces of good."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "You gain a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. Heretic has 6 charges for the following properties; the sword regains 1d4 + 1 charges daily at dawn:"
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Destroy Devotion."
        , T " Once per turn when you hit a creature with this weapon, you can expend 1 of its charges to attempt to render the target powerless. The target must succeed on a DC 17 Constitution saving throw or have the paralyzed condition until the start of your next turn. Celestials have disadvantage on the save."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Faith Hunter."
        , T " While holding the sword, you can use an action to expend 1 or more of its charges to cast one of the following spells from it: "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:detect-evil-and-good" "Detect Evil and Good"
        , T " (1 charge), "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:fly" "Fly"
        , T " (2 charges), or "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:true-seeing" "True Seeing"
        , T " (3 charges)."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Sentience."
        , T " Heretic is a sentient, chaotic evil weapon with an Intelligence of 17, a Wisdom of 17, and a Charisma of 15. It has hearing and darkvision out to a range of 120 feet."
        , T "\nThe weapon can speak, read, and understand Common and Giant, and it can communicate with its wielder telepathically. Its voice is soft and deep but rises in a wild furor when it's aware Celestials or worshipers of good-aligned deities are present. While you are attuned to it, Heretic also understands every language you know."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Personality."
        , T " Heretic craves the destruction of good-aligned gods and their supporters. The blade is condescending and snobby, especially in the company of priests and other pious folk, at whom it often directs sneering comments. When Heretic identifies its quarry, it erupts in a frenzied need for violence."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Hide of the Feral Guardian"
