    , source: [SourceStormKingsThunder]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, legendary (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The "
        , I "Korolnor Scepter"
        , T " is one of ten Ruling Scepters of Shanatar, forged by the dwarven gods and given to the ruling houses of the ancient dwarven empire. The "
        , I "Korolnor Scepter"
        , T "'s location was unknown for the longest time until a storm giant queen, Neri, found it in a barnacle-covered shipwreck at the bottom of the Trackless Sea. The Ruling Scepters are all roughly the same size and shape, but their materials and properties vary."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The "
        , I "Korolnor Scepter"
        , T " is a tapered mithral rod as thick and long as a dwarf's forearm, with a small platinum knob at the bottom and a rounded disk adorned with a ring of seven tiny blue gems at the top."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "You gain a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this scepter, which can be wielded as a magic club."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "You can use the properties of the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/wondrous-items:wyrmskull-throne" "Wyrmskull Throne"
        , T ", as well as the properties of the scepter itself. The scepter has 10 charges, and it regains 1d6 + 4 expended charges at dawn. Its properties are as follows:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "If you are underground or underwater, you can use an action to expend 1 charge to determine the distance to the surface."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "As an action, you can expend 2 charges to cast the "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:sending" "Sending"
          , T " spell from the scepter."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "As an action, you can expend 3 charges to cast the "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:teleport" "Teleport"
          , T " spell from the scepter. If the destination is within 60 feet of the "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/wondrous-items:wyrmskull-throne" "Wyrmskull Throne"
          , T ", there is no chance of a teleport error or mishap occurring."
          ]
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Longbow of the Healing Hearth"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:longbow-of-the-healing-hearth"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeWeapon (Just "longbow")
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceBigbyPresentsGloryOfTheGiants]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Weapon (Longbow), Legendary (Requires Attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "This ivory longbow is inscribed with a prayer to the god Hiatea, the runes of which are entwined with gilded engravings of wheat stalks and deer antlers."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "You gain a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this weapon. If you load no ammunition in the weapon, it produces its own, automatically creating one magic arrow when you pull back the string. The arrow created by the bow vanishes the instant after it hits or misses a target."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The bow has 8 charges for the following properties, which you can use while wielding the bow. The bow regains 1d4 + 1 charges daily at dawn."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Curative Arrow."
        , T " When you take the Attack action using the bow, you can expend 1 charge to replace one of your attacks with a blazing arrow of curative magic, which automatically hits one creature you can see within 150 feet of you. The target can then immediately spend and roll one of its unspent Hit Dice and regain a number of hit points equal to the roll plus your Wisdom modifier (minimum of +1). If the target has no unspent Hit Dice remaining, nothing happens. You can use a curative arrow only once per turn."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Spellcasting."
        , T " While holding the bow, you can use an action to expend 1 or more of its charges to cast one of the following spells from it (save DC 18): "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:create-food-and-water" "Create Food and Water"
        , T " (1 charge), "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:warding-bond" "Warding Bond"
        , T " (2 charges), "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:guardian-of-faith" "Guardian of Faith"
        , T " (3 charges)."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Lost Crown of Besilmer"
