      , P
        [ B "Eyes of Midnight."
        , T " You have darkvision with a range of 60 feet. If you already have darkvision, its range increases by 60 feet."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Midnight Shroud."
        , T " The weapon has 6 charges. When you hit a creature with an attack using this weapon, you can expend one charge to force the creature to make a DC 20 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, the creature is blinded until the start of your next turn. The weapon regains 1d6 expended charges daily at dawn."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Nightfall Pearl"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:nightfall-pearl"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceExplorersGuideToWildemount]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, legendary (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Used to summon night, this 6-inch-diameter, jet-black orb is cold to the touch. You can spend 10 minutes to activate it, causing the area within 10 miles of it at the moment of activation to become night even if it is daytime. This night lasts for 24 hours, until you cancel it as an action, or until your attunement to the pearl ends. Once used, the pearl can't be used again for 24 hours."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Obsidian Flint Dragon Plate"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:obsidian-flint-dragon-plate"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeArmor Nothing
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceBaldursGateDescentIntoAvernus]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Armor (plate), legendary"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "You gain a +2 bonus to AC and resistance to poison damage while you wear this armor. ln addition, you gain advantage on ability checks and saving throws made to avoid or end the grappled condition on yourself."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Orb of Skoraeus"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:orb-of-skoraeus"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune (Just "spellcaster")
    , source: [SourceBigbyPresentsGloryOfTheGiants]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous Item, Legendary (Requires Attunement by a Spellcaster)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Said to be infused with the wisdom and power of the god Skoraeus, this polished stone orb is veined with iridescent crystal that seems to glow from within. The orb is 8 inches in diameter and weighs 8 pounds, making it a palm-sized trinket for a stone giant but a more unwieldy item for a Medium creature to use."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "While holding this orb, you can use it as a spellcasting focus for your spells. You also gain the following benefits:"
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Abundant Components."
        , T " The orb has 3 charges and regains all expended charges at dawn. When you cast a spell while holding this orb, you can expend up to 3 charges to ignore the spell's material components with a gold piece cost, up to 300 gp per charge expended."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Astute Mind."
        , T " You gain a +2 bonus to any Constitution saving throw you make to maintain your concentration on a spell."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Divine Sight."
        , T " You can see normally in darkness, both magical and nonmagical, to a distance of 120 feet."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Orcsplitter"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:orcsplitter"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeWeapon (Just "greataxe")
    , attunement: Attune (Just "good-aligned dwarf, fighter, or paladin")
    , source: [SourcePrincesOfTheApocalypse]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Weapon (greataxe), legendary (requires attunement by a good-aligned dwarf, fighter, or paladin)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "A mighty axe wielded long ago by the dwarf king Torhild Flametongue, "
        , I "Orcsplitter"
        , T " is a battered weapon that appears unremarkable at first glance. Its head is graven with the Dwarvish runes for \"orc,\" but the runes are depicted with a gap or slash through the markings; the word \"orc\" is literally split in two."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "You gain the following benefits while holding this magic weapon:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "You gain a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with it."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "When you roll a 20 on an attack roll with this weapon against an orc, that orc must succeed on a DC 17 Constitution saving throw or drop to 0 hit points."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "You can't be surprised by orcs while you're not incapacitated. You are also aware when orcs are within 120 feet of you and aren't behind total cover, although you don't know their location."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "You and any of your friends within 30 feet of you can't be frightened while you're not incapacitated."
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Sentience."
        , I "Orcsplitter"
        , T " is a sentient, lawful good weapon with an Intelligence of 6, a Wisdom of 15, and a Charisma of 10. It can see and hear out to 120 feet and has darkvision. It communicates by transmitting emotions to its wielder, although on rare occasions it uses a limited form of telepathy to bring to the wielder's mind a couplet or stanza of ancient Dwarvish verse."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Personality."
        , I "Orcsplitter"
        , T " is grim, taciturn, and inflexible. It knows little more than the desire to face orcs in battle and serve a courageous, just wielder. It disdains cowards and any form of duplicity, deception, or disloyalty. The weapon's purpose is to defend dwarves and to serve as a symbol of dwarven resolve. It hates the traditional foes of dwarves - giants, goblins, and, most of all, orcs - and silently urges its possessor to meet such creatures in battle."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Plate Armor of Etherealness"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:plate-armor-of-etherealness"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeArmor Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceDMG]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Armor (plate), legendary (requires attunement)"
        ]
