  , { title: "Ruby Weave Gem"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:ruby-weave-gem"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune (Just "spellcaster")
    , source: [SourceFizbansTreasuryOfDragons]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous Item, Legendary (Requires Attunement by a Spellcaster)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "While you are holding this gem, you can use it as a spellcasting focus for your spells."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The gem has 3 charges and regains all expended charges daily at dawn. When you cast a spell while holding this gem, you can expend up to 3 charges to ignore the spell's material components with a gold piece cost, up to 500 gp per charge expended."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "When you finish a long rest, choose a spell from any class list. The spell you choose must be of a level you can cast. You know the chosen spell and can cast it with your spell slots of the appropriate level until the end of your next long rest."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Ruinblade"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:ruinblade"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeWeapon (Just "greatsword")
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceInfernalMachineRebuild]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Weapon (greatsword), legendary (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ I "Ruinblade"
        , T " is a unique weapon possessed by Moghadam, the architect of the Tomb of Horrors. A symbol of his authority, Moghadam carries the weapon during the time frame of the adventure to intimidate the tomb's workers. (In later years, after Acererak trapped Moghadam in the completed tomb as an undead archwraith, Moghadam was able to use the weapon as his own phylactery.)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "A small jade version of the green devil face of the Tomb of Horrors is fashioned into the hilt of the weapon, with the blade extending from its open mouth. The blade always appears ruined and rusting, and causes its surroundings to appear reflected in the blade as if in a state of decay."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "You gain a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. When you hit an undead creature with it, the attack deals an extra 1d8 force damage."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "In addition, the weapon has the following properties:"
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Blighted Ruin."
        , T " You can cast the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:blight" "Blight"
        , T " spell from the weapon (DC 15). Once used, this property of the weapon can't be used until the next dawn."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Destructive Ruin."
        , T " You can cast the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:disintegrate" "Disintegrate"
        , T " spell from the weapon, but can target only a nonmagical object or a creation of magical force. Once used, this property of the weapon can't be used until dawn seven days later."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Curse."
        , T " This weapon is cursed, and becoming attuned to it extends the curse to you. Until the curse is broken with a "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:remove-curse" "Remove Curse"
        , T " spell or similar magic, you are unwilling to part with the weapon."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The weapon must take direct part in the destruction of 1,000 gp worth of materials and objects every seven days, or a conflict arises between you and the weapon at the end of the seventh day."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Sentience."
        , I "Ruinblade"
        , T " is a sentient lawful evil weapon with an Intelligence of 15, a Wisdom of 8, and a Charisma of 16. It has hearing and darkvision out to a range of 120 feet."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The weapon can speak, read, and understand Common, and can communicate with its wielder telepathically. Its voice is a rough, ruined echo. While you are attuned to it, "
        , I "Ruinblade"
        , T " also understands every language you know."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Personality."
        , I "Ruinblade"
        , T " speaks either with a dolorous or frenetic tone, depending on its mood. That mood improves when the sword is actively engaged in acts of destruction, but worsens if the blade is left inactive too long."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The weapon's purpose is to ruin and unmake existing objects, so that its owner can rebuild the world from a blank slate. It thus encourages its wielder to engage in constant destruction, claiming that this will allow the creation of a more superior vision from the ruin of what came before."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Scarab of Protection"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:scarab-of-protection"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceDMG]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, legendary (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "If you hold this beetle-shaped medallion in your hand for 1 round, an inscription appears on its surface revealing its magical nature. It provides two benefits while it is on your person:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "You have advantage on saving throws against spells."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "The scarab has 12 charges. If you fail a saving throw against a necromancy spell or a harmful effect originating from an undead creature, you can use your reaction to expend 1 charge and turn the failed save into a successful one. The scarab crumbles into powder and is destroyed when its last charge is expended."
          ]
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Scroll of Tarrasque Summoning"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:scroll-of-tarrasque-summoning"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeScroll
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceIcewindDaleRimeOfTheFrostmaiden]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Scroll, legendary"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Using an action to read the scroll causes the tarrasque (see the creature's entry in the "
        , I "Monster Manual"
        , T ") to appear in an unoccupied space you can see within 1 mile of you. The tarrasque disappears when it drops to 0 hit points and is hostile toward all creatures other than itself."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Scroll of the Comet"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:scroll-of-the-comet"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeScroll
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceIcewindDaleRimeOfTheFrostmaiden]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Scroll, legendary"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "By using an action to read the scroll, you cause a comet to fall from the sky and crash to the ground at a point you can see up to 1 mile away from you. You must be outdoors when you use the scroll, or nothing happens and the scroll is wasted."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The comet creates a 50-foot-deep, 500-foot-radius crater on impact. Any creature in that radius must make a DC 20 Dexterity saving throw, taking 30d10 force damage on a failed saving throw, or half as much damage on a successful one. All structures in the crater are destroyed, as are all nonmagical objects that aren't being worn or held."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Shard Solitaire"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:shard-solitaire"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceKeysFromTheGoldenVault]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous Item, Legendary (Requires Attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "This gemstone contains an unstable extradimensional rift. Its facets are ribboned with iridescent veins that seem to move of their own accord. Five types of "
        , I "shard solitaire"
        , T " are known to exist, each one a different type of gemstone, as shown in the Shard Solitaire Types table."
        ]
      , P
        [ I "Rift Step."
        , T " As a bonus action, while wearing or holding the "
        , I "shard solitaire"
        , T ", you can teleport yourself, along with anything you're wearing or carrying, to an unoccupied space you can see within 30 feet of yourself."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "When you use this property, you can tap into the unstable power of the stone's extradimensional rift to increase the teleport distance by up to 30 feet, but if you teleport more than 30 feet using Rift Step, you must succeed on a DC 16 Constitution saving throw or take 3d10 force damage immediately after you teleport."
        ]
      , P
        [ I "Spellcasting."
        , T " The stone has 6 charges and regains 1d6 expended charges daily at dawn. The Shard Solitaire Types table lists the spells common to all "
        , I "shard solitaires"
        , T ", as well as the spells specific to each kind of stone. As an action, you can cast one of the stone's spells by expending the requisite number of charges, requiring no material components (save DC 16)."
        ]
      , TB
        [ T "Shard Solitaire Types"
        ]
        [           []
        , 
          [ T "All"
          , T "Banishment (3 charges; the target is banished to the stone's extradimensional space for the spell's duration), Mirror Image (1 charge)"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Black Sapphire"
          , T "Blight (3 charges), Finger of Death (6 charges)"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Diamond"
          , T "Ice Storm (3 charges), Simulacrum (6 charges; the duplicate created by the spell has the same number of hit points as the creature it imitates)"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Jacinth"
          , T "Fireball (2 charges), Fire Storm (6 charges)"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Rainbow Pearl"
          , T "Prismatic Spray (6 charges), Water Breathing (2 charges)"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Ruby"
          , T "Fly (2 charges), Teleport (6 charges)"
          ]
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Shield of the Blazing Dreadnought"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:shield-of-the-blazing-dreadnought"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeArmor Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceBigbyPresentsGloryOfTheGiants]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Armor (Shield), Legendary (Requires Attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Modeled after the formidable spiked tower shields wielded by some fire giants, this iron shield emanates a constant warmth."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "You can use a bonus action to activate the shield, causing glowing lava to flow through the shield's grooves for 1 minute. While the shield is active, you gain the following benefits:"
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Blazing Soul."
        , T " You have immunity to fire damage."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Cleansing Fire."
        , T " As an action, you can cause the shield to flare with the cleansing fire of the god Surtur. Choose one creature you can see within 30 feet of yourself (you can choose yourself). One disease or condition of your choice affecting this creature ends immediately; the condition can be blinded, charmed, deafened, or poisoned."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Shield Bash."
        , T " When you take the Attack action on your turn, you can replace one of your attacks with a shield bash, targeting one creature you can see within 5 feet of yourself. The target must make a Strength saving throw (DC equals 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Strength modifier). On a failed save, the target takes 3d6 bludgeoning damage plus 3d6 fire damage and is knocked prone. On a successful save, the target takes half as much damage only. You can use Shield Bash only once per turn."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Once the shield has been activated, it can't be activated again until the next dawn."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Shield of the Hidden Lord"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:shield-of-the-hidden-lord"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeArmor Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceBaldursGateDescentIntoAvernus]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Armor (shield), legendary (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The "
        , I "Shield of the Hidden Lord"
        , T " is of celestial origin and serves as a prison for the pit fiend Gargauth, whose mortal followers revere it as a god. Over time, Gargauth's evil has warped the shield's appearance, so that its celestial motif and designs have become twisted into a fiendish face that subtly moves in disturbing ways."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "While holding this shield, you gain a +2 bonus to AC and resistance to fire damage."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Sentience."
        , T " The "
        , I "Shield of the Hidden Lord"
        , T " is sentient as long as it imprisons Gargauth. While sentient, the shield has the following properties:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "The shield has an Intelligence of 22, a Wisdom of 18, and a Charisma of 24, as well as hearing and truesight out to a range of 120 feet."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "The shield can speak, read, and understand Common and Infernal, and it can communicate telepathically with any creature it can sense within 120 feet of it. Its voice is a deep, hollow whisper."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "The shield has 3 charges. You can use an action to expend 1 charge to cast "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:fireball" "Fireball"
          , T " or 2 charges to cast "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:wall-of-fire" "Wall of Fire"
          , T " from the shield (save DC 21 for each). The wall of fire spell lasts for 1 minute (no concentration required). The shield regains all expended charges daily at dawn."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Anytime during your turn, the shield can choose to radiate an aura of dread for 1 minute. (This is not a power of the shield that you control.) Any creature hostile to you that starts its turn within 20 feet of the shield must make a DC 18 Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature is frightened until the start of its next turn. On a successful save, the creature is immune to this power of the shield for the next 24 hours. Once the shield uses this power, it can't use it again until the next dawn."
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Gargauth's Personality."
        , T " Gargauth desperately seeks freedom but can't escape on its own. The pit fiend won't reveal its true nature, referring to itself only as the Hidden Lord. It drops hints and subtle suggestions that it is an angel trapped in an unholy prison. If released from the shield, the pit fiend honors the terms of whatever bargain it struck to facilitate its escape."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "While trapped in the shield, Gargauth carefully steers the shield's current owner toward committing acts of cruelty and domination, hoping to condemn the individual's soul to the Nine Hells. Conflict occurs if the shield's owner does anything that would make it more difficult for Gargauth to escape its prison, such as leaving the shield in a place where others are unlikely to find it."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Gargauth doesn't know how to escape from the shield. The pit fiend believes (incorrectly) that it can break free of the shield if it's brought to the Nine Hells, for it's convinced that the shield's powers are weaker there."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Freeing Gargauth."
        , T " Casting "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:dispel-evil-and-good" "Dispel Evil and Good"
        , T " on the shield has a 1 percent chance of freeing the pit fiend, or automatically succeeds if the spell is cast by a solar, a planetar, or an archdevil. A god can release the pit fiend by touching the shield and speaking Gargauth's name. When released, Gargauth appears in a random, unoccupied space as close to the shield as possible."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Snicker-Snack"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:snicker-snack"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeWeapon (Just "greatsword")
    , attunement: Attune (Just "non-evil creature")
    , source: [SourceTheWildBeyondTheWitchlight]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Weapon (Greatsword), Legendary (Requires Attunement by a Non-evil Creature)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "You gain a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic vorpal sword. In addition, the weapon ignores resistance to slashing damage."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "When you use this weapon to attack a creature that has at least one head and roll a 20 on the attack roll, you cut off one of the creature's heads. The creature dies if it can't survive without the lost head. A creature is immune to this effect if it is immune to slashing damage, it doesn't have or need a head, it has legendary actions, or the DM decides that the creature is too big for its head to be cut off with this weapon. Such a creature instead takes an extra 6d8 slashing damage from the hit."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "While attuned to "
        , I "Snicker-Snack"
        , T ", you have proficiency with greatswords, and you can use your Charisma modifier instead of your Strength modifier for attack and damage rolls made with the weapon."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Sentience."
        , I "Snicker-Snack"
        , T " is a sentient, chaotic good greatsword with an Intelligence of 9, a Wisdom of 14, and a Charisma of 18. It has hearing and darkvision out to a range of 120 feet. It can speak, read, and understand Common, and its voice sounds silvery and melodic. "
        , I "Snicker-Snack"
        , T " craves the destruction of evil Dragons and urges you to seek out these creatures and slay them."
        ]
      , P
        [ I "Snicker-Snack"
        , T " has a fickle personality. It ends its attunement to you if you miss on attack rolls with the weapon three times in a row. Each time you finish a long rest after that happens, you can attempt to regain the sword's trust by making a contested Charisma check against "
        , I "Snicker-Snack"
        , T ". If you win the contest, your attunement to the weapon is instantly restored. Your attunement to the weapon can't be restored in any other way."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Sovereign Glue"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:sovereign-glue"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceDMG]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, legendary"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "This viscous, milky-white substance can form a permanent adhesive bond between any two objects. It must be stored in a jar or flask that has been coated inside with "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/wondrous-items:oil-of-slipperiness" "Oil of Slipperiness"
        , T ". When found, a container contains 1d6 + 1 ounces."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "One ounce of the glue can cover a 1-foot square surface. The glue takes 1 minute to set. Once it has done so, the bond it creates can be broken only by the application of "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/wondrous-items:universal-solvent" "Universal Solvent"
        , T " or "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/wondrous-items:oil-of-etherealness" "Oil of Etherealness"
        , T ", or with a "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:wish" "Wish"
        , T " spell."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Spell Bottle"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:spell-bottle"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceExplorersGuideToWildemount]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, legendary (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "This glass bottle can store one spell of up to 5th level at a time. When found, roll a d6 and subtract 1: the total determines the level of spell in the bottle (the DM chooses the spell, and 0 means the bottle is empty). A swirling blue vapor fills the bottle while it contains a spell."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "When the bottle is empty, any creature can cast a spell of 1st through 5th level into it by touching it while casting. The spell has no effect other than to be stored in the bottle."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "While holding the bottle, you can cast the spell stored in it. The spell uses the slot level, spell save DC, spell attack bonus, and spellcasting ability of the original caster, but is otherwise treated as if you cast the spell. The bottle becomes empty once the spell is cast."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "If you're holding the empty bottle when you see a creature casting a spell within 60 feet of you, you can open the bottle as a reaction in an attempt to interrupt the spell. If the creature is casting a spell of 3rd level or lower, the spell has no effect, and it is stored in the bottle. If it is casting a spell of 4th level or higher, make an Intelligence check. The DC equals 10 + the spell's level. On a success, the spell has no effect, and it is stored in the bottle."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Sphere Of Annihilation"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:sphere-of-annihilation"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: AttuneNone
    , source: [SourceDMG]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, legendary"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "This 2-foot-diameter black sphere is a hole in the multiverse, hovering in space and stabilized by a magical field surrounding it."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The sphere obliterates all matter it passes through and all matter that passes through it. Artifacts are the exception. Unless an artifact is susceptible to damage from a "
        , I "sphere of annihilation"
        , T ", it passes through the sphere unscathed. Anything else that touches the sphere but isn't wholly engulfed and obliterated by it takes 4d10 force damage."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The sphere is stationary until someone controls it. If you are within 60 feet of an uncontrolled sphere, you can use an action to make a DC 25 Intelligence (Arcana) check. On a success, the sphere levitates in one direction of your choice, up to a number of feet equal to 5 x your Intelligence modifier (minimum 5 feet). On a failure, the sphere moves 10 feet toward you. A creature whose space the sphere enters must succeed on a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw or be touched by it, taking 4d10 force damage."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "If you attempt to control a sphere that is under another creature's control, you make an Intelligence (Arcana) check contested by the other creature's Intelligence (Arcana) check. The winner of the contest gains control of the sphere and can levitate it as normal."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "If the sphere comes into contact with a planar portal, such as that created by the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:gate" "Gate"
        , T " spell, or an extradimensional space, such as that within a "
