  , { title: "Ythryn Mythallar"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:ythryn-mythallar"
    , rarity: [RarityLegendary]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune (Just "spellcaster")
    , source: [SourceIcewindDaleRimeOfTheFrostmaiden]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, legendary (requires attunement by a spellcaster)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "A "
        , I "mythallar"
        , T " looks like an enormous crystal ball held in an ornate cradle. The globe sheds bright light in a 300-foot radius and dim light for an additional 300 feet. The globe draws magic from the Weave that can be harnessed for various purposes. For example, Netherese mages used "
        , I "mythallars"
        , T " to keep their cities aloft and empower their magic items. The bigger the "
        , I "mythallar"
        , T ", the more magic it can hold. The largest "
        , I "mythallars"
        , T " are 150 feet in diameter."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The "
        , I "Ythryn mythallar"
        , T " is a relatively small device - a mere 50 feet in diameter. To attune to this "
        , I "mythallar"
        , T ", a creature must finish a short rest within 30 feet of it, meditating on the "
        , I "mythallar"
        , T ". Up to eight creatures can be attuned to it at one time; otherwise, the "
        , I "Ythryn mythallar"
        , T " follows the attunement rules in the "
        , I "Dungeon Master's Guide"
        , T ". If a ninth creature tries to attune to the "
        , I "mythallar"
        , T ", nothing happens."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "All creatures attuned to the "
        , I "Ythryn mythallar"
        , T " can sense when the device is being used. A creature attuned to the device can use any of its properties, but only if all other creatures attuned to the device agree to allow it. The "
        , I "Ythryn mythallar's"
        , T " properties are as follows:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "While you're on the same plane of existence as the "
          , I "Ythryn mythallar"
          , T ", you can use an action to cause it to fly in any direction you choose at a speed of 30 feet. All matter within 500 feet of the device moves with it. The "
          , I "Ythryn mythallar"
          , T " and all structures held aloft by it hover in place when not in motion."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "As an action, you can cause one magic item you are holding within 30 feet of the "
          , I "Ythryn mythallar"
          , T " to immediately regain all its expended charges or uses. A magic item recharged in this manner can't be recharged by the "
          , I "Ythryn mythallar"
          , T " again until after the item regains expended charges or uses on its own."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "You can use the "
          , I "Ythryn mythallar"
          , T " to cast the "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:control-weather" "Control Weather"
          , T " spell without requiring any components and without the need for you to be outdoors. This casting of the spell has a 50-mile radius. For the duration of the spell's casting time, you must be within 30 feet of the "
          , I "Ythryn mythallar"
          , T " or the spell fails."
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Touching the Mythallar"
        , T ". Any creature that touches the globe of the "
        , I "mythallar"
        , T " must make a DC 22 Constitution saving throw, taking 180 (20d10 + 70) radiant damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. Undead have disadvantage on this saving throw. Any object that touches the globe, other than an artifact or the "
        , I "mythallar's"
        , T " cradle, is disintegrated instantly (no save)."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Adze of Annam"
