  , { title: "Crook of Rao"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:crook-of-rao"
    , rarity: [RarityArtifact]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceTashasCauldronOfEverything]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, artifact (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Ages ago, the serene god Rao created a tool to shield his fledgling faithful against the evils of the Lower Planes. Yet, as eons passed, mortals developed their own methods of dealing with existential threats, and the crook was largely forgotten. In recent ages, though, the "
        , I "Crook of Rao"
        , T " was rediscovered and leveraged against the rising power of the Witch Queen Iggwilv (one of the names of the wizard Tasha). Although she was defeated, Iggwilv managed to damage the crook during the battle, infecting it with an insidious curse - and the potential for future victory. In the aftermath, the crook was again lost. Occasionally it reappears, but the famed artifact is not what it was. Whether or not the artifact's bearers realize its full threat, few risk using the "
        , I "Crook of Rao"
        , T " - potentially for the final time."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Random Properties."
        , T " The artifact has the following random properties, which you can determine by rolling on the tables in the \"Artifacts\" section of the "
        , I "Dungeon Master's Guide"
        , T ":"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "2 minor beneficial properties"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "1 major beneficial property"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "1 minor detrimental property"
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Spells."
        , T " The crook has 6 charges. While holding it, you can use an action to expend 1 or more of its charges to cast one of the following spells (save DC 18) from it: "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:aura-of-life" "Aura of Life"
        , T " (2 charges), "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:aura-of-purity" "Aura of Purity"
        , T " (2 charges), "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:banishment" "Banishment"
        , T " (1 charge), "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:beacon-of-hope" "Beacon of Hope"
        , T " (1 charge), "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:mass-cure-wounds" "Mass Cure Wounds"
        , T " (3 charges). The crook regains 1d6 expended charges daily at dawn."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Absolute Banishment."
        , T " While you are attuned to the crook and holding it, you can spend 10 minutes to banish all but the mightiest fiends within 1 mile of you. Any fiend with a challenge rating of 19 or higher is unaffected. Each banished fiend is sent back to its home plane and can't return to the plane the "
        , I "Crook of Rao"
        , T " banished it from for 100 years."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Failing Matrix."
        , T " Whenever the Crook of Rao's Absolute Banishment property is used, or when its last charge is expended, roll on the Extraplanar Reversal table. Any creatures conjured as a result of this effect appear in random unoccupied spaces within 60 feet of you and are not under your control."
        ]
      , TB
        [ T "Extraplanar Reversal"
        ]
        [           []
        , 
          [ T "01-25"
          , T "A portal to a random plane opens. The portal closes after 5 minutes."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "26-45"
          , T "2d4 imps and 2d4 quasits appear."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "46-60"
          , T "1d8 succubi/incubi appear."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "61-70"
          , T "1d10 barbed devils and 1d10 vrocks appear."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "71-80"
          , T "1 arcanoloth, 1 night hag, and 1 rakshasa appear."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "81-85"
          , T "1 ice devil and 1 marilith appear."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "86-90"
          , T "1 balor and 1 pit fiend appear. At the DM's discretion, a portal opens into the presence of an archdevil or demon lord instead, then closes after 5 minutes."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "91-00"
          , T "Iggwilv's Curse (see the Iggwilv's Curse property)."
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Iggwilv's Curse."
        , T " When the Crook was last used against Iggwilv, the Witch Queen lashed out at the artifact, infecting its magical matrix. Over the years, this curse has spread within the crook, threatening to violently pervert its ancient magic. If this occurs, the "
        , I "Crook of Rao"
        , T ", as it is currently known, is destroyed, its magical matrix inverting and exploding into a 50-foot-diameter portal. This portal functions as a permanent gate spell cast by Iggwilv. The gate then, once per round on initiative count 20, audibly speaks a fiend's name in lggwilv's voice, doing so until the gate calls on every fiend ever banished by the "
        , I "Crook of Rao"
        , T ". If the fiend still exists, it is drawn through the gate. This process takes eighteen years to complete, at the end of which the gate becomes a permanent portal to Pazunia, the first layer of the Abyss."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Destroying or Repairing the Crook."
        , T " The "
        , I "Crook of Rao"
        , T " can either be destroyed or repaired by journeying to Mount Celestia and obtaining a tear from the eternally serene god Rao. One way to make the emotionless god cry would be to reunite Rao with the spirit of his first worshiper who sought revelations beyond the multiverse long ago. The Crook dissolves if immersed in the god's tear for a year and a day. If washed in the tear daily for 30 days, the Crook loses its Failing Matrix property."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Crown of Lies"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:crown-of-lies"
    , rarity: [RarityArtifact]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceVecnaEyeOfRuin]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous Item, Artifact (Requires Attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "After betraying and nearly destroying the lich Vecna, the warrior Kas found himself trapped in the Shadowfell, imprisoned in a Domain of Dread called Tovag. There, he languished as a vampire."
        , T "\nIn time, the Dark Powers of the Shadowfell lured Kas to a hidden forge, where he found the Crown of Lies. Once Kas vowed to deliver Vecna into the Dark Powers' clutches and donned the crown, the Dark Powers released Kas. From there, Kas set out to ruin his former master. Should Kas fail, the Dark Powers will reclaim him."
        , T "\nThe crown is made of burnished and entwined metal rods. To attune to it, you must place it on your head and speak a true desire of your heart. You know how to attune to the crown when you touch it."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Random Properties."
        , T " The Crown of Lies has the following random properties (see the Dungeon Master's Guide for options)"
        , T "\n1 minor beneficial property"
        , T "\n1 major beneficial property"
        , T "\n1 minor detrimental property"
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Perfect Disguise"
        , T ". While attuned to the crown, you can use an action to transform yourself to look and feel like any creature you've seen at least once and whose size is no more than one size smaller or larger than yours."
        , T "\nThe new form mimics the chosen creature's appearance exactly, including its voice. Your size and speed are replaced by the chosen creature's. You otherwise retain your own game statistics. While in this new form, the crown melds into your person and is undetectable."
        , T "\nYour new form lasts until you die, your attunement to the crown ends, or you use another action to transform into a different creature or your true form. Interactions with you while you are transformed by the crown reveal no illusory magic, nor do they reveal anything other than details about the creature you're disguised as. You count as the chosen creature for the purposes of spells, traps, and other defenses that wouldn't target the chosen creature."
        , T "\nWhile in your disguised form, any lies you tell always seem to be true, no matter what magical or mundane methods are used to try to detect your falsehoods. You are the recipient of "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:sending" "Sending"
        , T " spells addressed to you and the creature you are disguised as, and Scrying and similar spells that target the creature you are disguised as actually target you. The only way to reveal your true nature while transformed by the crown is with a "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:wish" "Wish"
        , T " spell."
        , T "\nWhile wearing this crown in your true form, you can choose for the crown to be visible if you wish."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Destroying the Crown."
        , T " If a creature wearing the crown is killed by the creature it is disguised as, the crown disintegrates and is destroyed."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Daoud's Wondrous Lantern"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:daouds-wondrous-lantern"
    , rarity: [RarityArtifact]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceQuestsFromTheInfiniteStaircase]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, artifact (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "This artifact destroys wealth to provide light and protection. Wrought from the finest yellow gold, the lantern has four faces, and an unwavering amber flame burns within it. The faces of the lantern are fitted with faceted gemstone lenses."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The lantern is a symbol of the teachings of Daoud, who was once a priest of Istus, a god of fate. When Daoud was stripped of his possessions, he developed a radical new philosophy in his quest to understand fate. He urged followers of his ideology to eschew wealth and seek out all fortunes, good and ill, to unravel the cloth of destiny."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Random Properties."
        , T " The lantern has the following random properties:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "2 minor beneficial properties"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "1 major beneficial property"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "1 minor detrimental property"
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Precious Fuel."
        , T " The lantern burns only one source of fuel: powdered gemstones placed in the lantern's base. The lantern can hold a maximum of 10,000 gp worth of powdered gems, and it contains 9,000 gp of fuel when found. Thereafter it attempts to burn 100 gp of fuel after each year passes, keeping the lantern burning for another year. If no fuel is available, the lantern's flame goes out. You can add more fuel to the lantern as part of a short or long rest. Once added, fuel can't be removed from the lantern's base."
        , T "\nThe lantern's flame can't be extinguished by any means other than running out of fuel. If the lantern's flame goes out, the creature attuned to it immediately dies. One exception to this rule exists (see the \"Destroying the Lantern\" section)."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Revealing Light."
        , T " The lantern sheds bright light in a 60-foot radius and dim light for an additional 60 feet. Invisible creatures and objects are visible while in the lantern's bright light."
        , T "\nWhile attuned to the lantern, you can use a bonus action to dim the lantern, reducing the light to dim light in a 5-foot radius, or brighten the lantern back to its normal bright light radius."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Lenses."
        , T " When found, the lantern's faces display the following gem lenses: diamond, emerald, ruby, and sapphire. As part of a short or long rest, you can magically change any of these gem lenses to a different type of gem shown in the Lenses table. The gem lenses can't be removed from the lantern."
        , T "\nAs an action while holding the lantern, you can burn some of the lantern's fuel to cast a spell (save DC 20) through one or more of its current gem lenses, as noted in the Lenses table. The spell's target or point of origin must be in the lantern's area of bright light. If there isn't enough fuel left to cast the spell, the last of the remaining fuel is expended, and the flame goes out."
        ]
      , T "\nLenses"
      , TB
        [ T "Lens Color"
        , T "Spell"
        , T "Fuel Cost"
        ]
        [ 
          [ T "Amethyst"
          , T "Reverse Gravity"
          , T "3000gp"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Diamond"
          , T "Disintegrate"
          , T "2000gp"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Emerald"
          , T "Haste"
          , T "500gp"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Jacinth"
          , T "Flame Strike"
          , T "1000gp"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Ruby"
          , T "Hold Monster"
          , T "1000gp"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Sapphire"
          , T "Fear"
          , T "500gp"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Topaz"
          , T "Slow"
          , T "500gp"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Any four colors"
          , T "Prismatic Wall"
          , T "5000gp"
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Destroying the Lantern."
        , T " To destroy the lantern, the creature attuned to it must forsake all material possessions except for the lantern and common clothes. Then the creature must willingly snuff the lantern's flame with the intention to destroy the artifact. When its flame is snuffed in this way, the lantern's gold corrodes, the lenses and remaining gemstone fuel turn to worthless sand, and the creature attuned to it is spared."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Dekella, Bident of Thassa"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:dekella"
    , rarity: [RarityArtifact]
    , itemtype: TypeWeapon (Just "trident")
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceMythicOdysseysOfTheros]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Weapon (trident), artifact (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Thassa wields "
        , I "Dekella"
        , T ", a two-pronged weapon gifted to her by Purphoros. When the god of the sea bestows her weapon on a mortal, it's often so they might work her will far from the ocean, right some wrong affecting those she'd prefer not to harm, or give a mortal a glimpse of her terrible responsibilities."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Bident of the Deep."
        , T " Thassa's signature weapon thrums with the icy currents of the deep ocean. This weapon functions as a trident that grants a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with it. When you hit with an attack using the bident, the target takes an extra 2d10 cold damage."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Blessing of the Deep."
        , T " If you are a worshiper of Thassa, you gain all the following benefits for which you have the required piety:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ B "Piety 10+."
          , T " You can breathe underwater, and you gain a swimming speed of 60 feet."
          ]
        , 
          [ B "Piety 25+."
          , T " The bident has 1 randomly determined minor beneficial property."
          ]
        , 
          [ B "Piety 50+."
          , T " The bident has 1 randomly determined major beneficial property."
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ T "If you aren't a worshiper of Thassa, the bident has 1 minor detrimental property and 1 major detrimental property, both randomly determined."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "See \"Artifacts\" in chapter 7 of the "
        , I "Dungeon Master's Guide"
        , T " for details on randomly determined properties."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Command the Deep."
        , T " The bident holds the power to command the waves and its creatures. As an action, you can change the condition of the sea within 1 mile of you, creating strong winds and heavy rain that cause violent waves (see \"Weather at Sea\" in chapter 5 of the "
        , I "Dungeon Master's Guide"
        , T ") or calming a storm. In either case, the unnatural weather lasts for 1 hour before returning to normal. Once used, this property of the bident can't be used again until the next dusk."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Additionally, you can cast the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:dominate-monster" "Dominate Monster"
        , T " spell (save DC 18) from the bident, but only on beasts and monstrosities that have an innate swimming speed. Once used, this property of the bident can't be used again until the next dusk."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Aquatic Metamorphosis."
        , T " You can cast the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:true-polymorph" "True Polymorph"
        , T " spell (save DC 18) from the bident, but you must cast it on a creature to turn it into a kind of creature that has an innate swimming speed. Once used, this property of the bident can't be used again until the next dusk."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Destroying the Bident."
        , T " To destroy the bident, it must be heated by the breath of an ancient red dragon and then, while still hot, immersed in the Tartyx River."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Demonomicon of Iggwilv"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:demonomicon-of-iggwilv"
    , rarity: [RarityArtifact]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceTashasCauldronOfEverything]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, artifact (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "An expansive treatise documenting the Abyss's infinite layers and inhabitants, the "
        , I "Demonomicon of lggwilv"
        , T " is the most thorough and blasphemous tome of demonology in the multiverse. The tome recounts both the oldest and most current profanities of the Abyss and demons. Demons have attempted to censor the text, and while sections have been ripped from the book's spine, the general chapters remain, ever revealing demonic secrets. And the book holds more than blasphemies. Caged behind lines of script roils a secret piece of the Abyss itself, which keeps the book up-to-date, no matter how many pages are removed, and it longs to be more than mere reference material."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Random Properties."
        , T " The artifact has the follow random properties, which you can determine by rolling on the tables in the \"Artifacts\" section of the "
        , I "Dungeon Master's Guide"
        , T ":"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "2 minor beneficial properties"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "1 minor detrimental property"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "1 major detrimental property"
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Spells."
        , T " The book has 8 charges. It regains 1d8 expended charges daily at dawn. While holding it, you can use an action to cast "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:tashas-hideous-laughter" "Tasha's Hideous Laughter"
        , T " from it or to expend 1 or more of its charges to cast one of the following spells (save DC 20) from it: "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:magic-circle" "Magic Circle"
        , T " (1 charge), "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:magic-jar" "Magic Jar"
        , T " (3 charges), "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:planar-ally" "Planar Ally"
        , T " (3 charges), "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:planar-binding" "Planar Binding"
        , T " (2 charges), "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:plane-shift" "Plane Shift"
        , T " (to layers of the Abyss only; 3 charges), "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:summon-fiend" "Summon Fiend"
        , T " (3 charges; appears in this book)."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Abyssal Reference."
        , T " You can reference the "
        , I "Demonomicon"
        , T " whenever you make an Intelligence check to discern information about demons or a Wisdom (Survival) check related to the Abyss. When you do so, you can add double your proficiency bonus to the check."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Fiendish Scourging."
        , T " Your magic causes pain to fiends. While carrying the book, when you make a damage roll for a spell you cast against a fiend, you use the maximum possible result instead of rolling."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Ensnarement."
        , T " While carrying the book, whenever you cast the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:magic-circle" "Magic Circle"
        , T " spell naming only fiends, or the "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:planar-binding" "Planar Binding"
        , T " spell targeting a fiend, the spell is cast at 9th level, regardless of what level spell slot you used, if any. Additionally, the fiend has disadvantage on its saving throw against the spell."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Containment."
        , T " The first 10 pages of the "
        , I "Demonomicon"
        , T " are blank. As an action while holding the book, you can target a fiend that you can see that is trapped within a "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:magic-circle" "Magic Circle"
        , T ". The fiend must succeed on a DC 20 Charisma saving throw with disadvantage or become trapped within one of the "
        , I "Demonomicon"
        , T "'s empty blank pages, which fills with writing detailing the trapped creature's widely known name and depravities. Once used, this action can't be used again until the next dawn."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "When you finish a long rest, if you and the "
        , I "Demonomicon"
        , T " are on the same plane of existence, the trapped creature of the highest challenge rating within the book can attempt to possess you. You must make a DC 20 Charisma saving throw. On a failure, you are possessed by the creature, which controls you like a puppet. The possessing creature can release you as an action, appearing in the closest unoccupied space. On a successful save, the fiend can't try to possess you again for 7 days."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "When the tome is discovered, it has 1d4 fiends occupying its pages, typically an assortment of demons."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Destroying the Demonomicon."
        , T " To destroy the book, six different demon lords must each tear out a sixth of the book's pages. If this occurs, the pages reappear after 24 hours. Before all those hours pass, anyone who opens the book's remaining binding is transported to a nascent layer of the Abyss that lies hidden within the book. At the heart of this deadly, semi-sentient domain lies a long-lost artifact, Fraz-Urb'luu's Staff. If the staff is dragged from the pocket plane, the tome is reduced to a mundane and quite out-of-date copy of the "
        , I "Tome of Zyx"
        , T ", the work that served as the foundation for the "
        , I "Demonomicon"
        , T ". Once the staff emerges, the demon lord Fraz-Urb'luu instantly knows."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Ephixis, Bow of Nyela"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:ephixis"
    , rarity: [RarityArtifact]
    , itemtype: TypeWeapon (Just "shortbow")
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceMythicOdysseysOfTheros]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Weapon (shortbow), artifact (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Nylea wields the shortbow "
        , I "Ephixis"
        , T ", the bow whose arrows herald the turning of the seasons. Nylea is quick to let her favored followers borrow her bow, particularly when they intend to use it to perform great deeds, put an end to foul creatures, or cast down the arrogant."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Bow of the Wild."
        , T " This divine weapon includes a shortbow and a quiver with four arrows, each tied to one of the four seasons. You gain a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this bow, and you suffer no disadvantage when attacking at the weapon's long range. Additionally, "
        , I "Ephixis"
        , T " scores a critical hit on a d20 roll of 19 or 20."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Blessing of the Wild."
        , T " If you are a worshiper of Nylea, you gain all the following benefits for which you have the required piety:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ B "Piety 10+."
          , T " The bow has 1 randomly determined minor beneficial property."
          ]
        , 
          [ B "Piety 25+."
          , T " The bow has 1 randomly determined major beneficial property."
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ T "If you aren't a worshiper of Nylea, the bow has 1 randomly determined major detrimental property."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "See \"Artifacts\" in chapter 7 of the "
        , I "Dungeon Master's Guide"
        , T " for details on randomly determined properties."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Arrows of the Seasons."
        , T " The four arrows - each associated with a season - that accompany this bow can be fired only from it. Each arrow disappears immediately after it's used, and it reappears in the quiver at the next dusk. The save DC against spells cast with the arrows is 18. Each arrow has a unique property:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ B "Spring."
          , T " As an action, you can fire this arrow, targeting a beast or a plant creature you can see within 320 feet of you. On a hit, the arrow deals no damage, and the target gains the benefits of the awaken spell for 8 hours."
          ]
        , 
          [ B "Summer."
          , T " As an action, you can fire this arrow at an unoccupied space on the ground that you can see within 320 feet of you, no attack roll required. A Nyxborn lynx is summoned in that space (use the stat block for a "
          , B "tiger"
          , T " with the Nyxborn traits from chapter 6 of MOT). The lynx understands your verbal commands and obeys them as best it can, and it takes its turns immediately after yours. The emissary remains for 1 hour before fading away."
          ]
        , 
          [ B "Autumn."
          , T " As an action, you can fire this arrow at a space on the ground that you can see within 320 feet of you, no attack roll required, casting the "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:wall-of-thorns" "Wall of Thorns"
          , T " spell there."
          ]
        , 
          [ B "Winter."
          , T " As an action, you can fire this arrow at a space that you can see within 320 feet of you, no attack roll required, casting the "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:ice-storm" "Ice Storm"
          , T " spell there."
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Destroying the Bow."
        , T " The bow can't be destroyed without first destroying all its arrows. The winter arrow must be fed to a cerberus on the winter solstice. The spring arrow must be planted at the base of a Black Oak of Asphodel on the spring equinox. The summer arrow must be broken by a sea giant on the summer solstice. Then the autumn arrow must be shot into the carcass of a hydra on the autumnal equinox. When all four arrows are destroyed, the bow and quiver dissolve into dust."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Eye and Hand of Vecna"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:eye-and-hand-of-vecna"
    , rarity: [RarityArtifact]
    , itemtype: TypeItem Nothing
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceDMG]
    , description:
      [ P
        [ I "Wondrous item, artifact (requires attunement)"
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Seldom is the name of Vecna spoken except in a hushed voice. Vecna was, in his time, one of the mightiest of all wizards. Through dark magic and conquest, he forged a terrible empire. For all his power, Vecna couldn't escape his own mortality. He began to fear death and take steps to prevent his end from ever coming about."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Orcus, the demon prince of undeath, taught Vecna a ritual that would allow him to live on as a lich. Beyond death, he became the greatest of all liches. Even though his body gradually withered and decayed, Vecna continued to expand his evil dominion. So formidable and hideous was his temper that his subjects feared to speak his name. He was the Whispered One, the Master of the Spider Throne, the Undying King, and the Lord of the Rotted Tower."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Some say that Vecna's lieutenant Kas coveted the Spider Throne for himself, or that the sword his lord made for him seduced him into rebellion. Whatever the reason, Kas brought the Undying King's rule to an end in a terrible battle that left Vecna's tower a heap of ash. Of Vecna, all that remained were one hand and one eye, grisly artifacts that still seek to work the Whispered One's will in the world."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "The "
        , I "Eye of Vecna"
        , T " and the "
        , I "Hand of Vecna"
        , T " might be found together or separately. The eye looks like a bloodshot organ torn free from the socket. The hand is a mummified and shriveled left extremity."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "To attune to the eye, you must gouge out your own eye and press the artifact into the empty socket. The eye grafts itself to your head and remains there until you die. Once in place, the eye transforms into a golden eye with a slit for a pupil, much like that of a cat. If the eye is ever removed, you die."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "To attune to the hand, you must lop off your left hand at the wrist and the press the artifact against the stump. The hand grafts itself to your arm and becomes a functioning appendage. If the hand is ever removed, you die."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Random Properties."
        , T " The "
        , I "Eye of Vecna"
        , T " and the "
        , I "Hand of Vecna"
        , T " each have the following random properties:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "1 minor beneficial property"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "1 major beneficial property"
          ]
        , 
          [ T "1 minor detrimental property"
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Properties of the Eye."
        , T " Your alignment changes to neutral evil, and you gain the following benefits:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "You have truesight."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "You can use an action to see as if you were wearing a "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/wondrous-items:ring-of-x-ray-vision" "Ring of X-Ray Vision"
          , T ". You can end this effect as a bonus action."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "The eye has 8 charges. You can use an action and expend 1 or more charges to cast one of the following spells (save DC 18) from it: "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:clairvoyance" "Clairvoyance"
          , T " (2 charges), "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:crown-of-madness" "Crown of Madness"
          , T " (1 charge), "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:disintegrate" "Disintegrate"
          , T " (4 charges), "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:dominate-monster" "Dominate Monster"
          , T " (5 charges), or "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:eyebite" "Eyebite"
          , T " (4 charges). The eye regains 1d4 + 4 expended charges daily at dawn. Each time you cast a spell from the eye, there is a 5 percent chance that Vecna tears your soul from your body, devours it, and then takes control of the body like a puppet. If that happens, you become an NPC under the DM's control."
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Properties of the Hand."
        , T " Your alignment changes to neutral evil, and you gain the following benefits:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "Your Strength score becomes 20, unless it is already 20 or higher."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Any melee spell attack you make with the hand, and any melee weapon attack made with a weapon held by it, deals an extra 2d8 cold damage on a hit."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "The hand has 8 charges. You can use an action and expend 1 or more charges to cast one of the following spells (save DC 18) from it: "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:finger-of-death" "Finger of Death"
          , T " (5 charges), "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:sleep" "Sleep"
          , T " (1 charge), "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:slow" "Slow"
          , T " (2 charges), or "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:teleport" "Teleport"
          , T " (3 charges). The hand regains 1d4 + 4 expended charges daily at dawn. Each time you cast a spell from the hand, it casts the "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:suggestion" "Suggestion"
          , T " spell on you (save DC 18), demanding that you commit an evil act. The hand might have a specific act in mind or leave it up to you."
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Properties of the Eye and Hand."
        , T " If you are attuned to both the hand and eye, you gain the following additional benefits:"
        ]
      , UL
        [ 
          [ T "You are immune to disease and poison."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "Using the eye's X-ray vision never causes you to suffer exhaustion."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "You experience premonitions of danger and, unless you are incapacitated, can't be surprised."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "If you start your turn with at least 1 hit point, you regain 1d10 hit points."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "If a creature has a skeleton, you can attempt to turn its bones to jelly with a touch of the "
          , I "Hand of Vecna"
          , T ". You can do so by using an action to make a melee attack against a creature you can reach, using your choice of your melee attack bonus for weapons or spells. On a hit, the target must succeed on a DC 18 Constitution saving throw or drop to 0 hit points."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "You can use an action to cast "
          , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:wish" "Wish"
          , T ". This property can't be used again until 30 days have passed."
          ]
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Destroying the Eye and Hand."
        , T " If the "
        , I "Eye of Vecna"
        , T " and the "
        , I "Hand of Vecna"
        , T " are both attached to the same creature, and that creature is slain by the Sword of Kas, both the eye and the hand burst into flame, turn to ash, and are destroyed forever. Any other attempt to destroy the eye or hand seems to work, but the artifact reappears in one of Vecna's many hidden vaults, where it waits to be rediscovered."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Grovelthrash"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:grovelthrash"
    , rarity: [RarityArtifact]
    , itemtype: TypeWeapon (Just "warhammer")
    , attunement: Attune Nothing
    , source: [SourceExplorersGuideToWildemount]
    , description:
