        , T ", "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:remove-curse" "Remove Curse"
        , T ", or similar spell ends the curse on the target."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "The Forgotten One."
        , T " The bodiless life force of a dead archmage empowers the staff and is imprisoned within it. The rune carved into the staff's skull protects Acererak from this spirit's vengeance. Each time a creature other than Acererak expends any of the staff's charges, there is a 50 percent chance that the life force tries to possess the staff wielder. The wielder must succeed on a DC 20 Charisma saving throw or be possessed, becoming an NPC under the DM's control. If the intruding life force is targeted by magic such as a "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/spell:dispel-evil-and-good" "Dispel Evil and Good"
        , T " spell, it becomes trapped in the staff once more. Once it takes control of another creature, the insane spirit of the dead archmage attempts to destroy the staff."
        ]
      , P
        [ B "Destroying the Staff."
        , T " A creature in possession of the staff can use an action to break it over one knee or a solid surface. The staff is destroyed and releases its remaining magic in an explosion that expands to fill a 30-foot-radius sphere centered on it. Each creature in the area must make a DC 18 Dexterity saving throw, taking 132 (24d10) force damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. When the staff is destroyed, the life force of the Forgotten One is released to the afterlife. Where it goes is anyone's guess."
        ]
      , P
        [ T "Casting the staff into a "
        , A "http://dnd5e.wikidot.com/wondrous-items:sphere-of-annihilation" "Sphere of Annihilation"
        , T " destroys both the staff and the Life force trapped within it. The staff doesn't explode if destroyed in this manner, but its destruction causes the sphere to be destroyed as well."
        ]
      ]
    }
  , { title: "Stone of Golorr"
    , url: "https://dnd5e.wikidot.com//wondrous-items:stone-of-golorr"
