        , 
          [ T "90"
          , T "Each time you finish a short rest, you find 1d10 small gems worth 10 gp each in your possession."
          , T "Whenever you spend coins or gems, any character you give them to becomes convinced that the wealth was stolen from them."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "91"
          , T "When you hit a creature for the first time during an encounter, its Armor Class is reduced by 1."
          , T "Whenever you roll a 1 on a weapon attack roll, the weapon shatters like glass. The weapon magically reforms in 1d4 rounds."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "92"
          , T "Each time you enter a settlement, you are treated as though you are known there and a friend, even if you are neither."
          , T "Each time you roll a 1 on an attack roll, ability check, or saving throw, you grow one inch taller. Your clothing and armor does not grow with you."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "93"
          , T "While standing in a doorway, you can cast the Teleport spell. Your destination must be another doorway you know. You can use this property once."
          , T "Each time you finish a short rest, you forget one of your allies (of the DM's choice) and no longer trust that character. You lose this distrust at the end of your next short rest."
          ]
        , 
          [ T "94"
          , T "As an action, you cause a swirling storm of rocks and dust to surround you in a 10-foot radius for 1 minute. Each creature hostile to you that enters the area must succeed on a DC 12 Constitution saving throw or take 1d6 bludgeoning damage and be blinded for 1 round. You can use this property three times."
